 Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin (via French  <b>Adélaïde</b> ), from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘kind, sort’. It was borne in the 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adelaide de Keynes was born about 1065, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Kahannes de Keynes Lord. She died about 1131, in her hometown, at the age of 68."},"et":{"ABT 1065–ABT 1131":"umbes 1065–umbes 1131","1065–1131":"1065–1131","1095–1170":"1095–1170","ABT 1065":"umbes 1065","ABT 1131":"umbes 1131","1131":"1131","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1065–ABT 1131":"noin 1065–noin 1131","1065–1131":"1065–1131","1095–1170":"1095–1170","ABT 1065":"noin 1065","ABT 1131":"noin 1131","1131":"1131","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, England"},"fr":{"ABT 1065–ABT 1131":"environ 1065–environ 1131","1065–1131":"1065–1131","1095–1170":"1095–1170","ABT 1065":"environ 1065","ABT 1131":"environ 1131","1131":"1131","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1170":"1170","Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, England":"Earls Barton, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Adelaide de Keynes est née environ 1065, à Northamptonshire, Angleterr